# Appendix N — SLAT for the community

Motoi Scheme is a language, and languages have subscribers. This
appendix covers the SLAT-shaped mechanisms that let dialect authors,
community forks, and downstream projects declare and share their
extensions.

## Subscriber declaration

```motoi-scheme
(subscriber
  :name         'baobab
  :repo         \"https://github.com/foundation/baobab\"
  :dialect      'motoi-scheme
  :dialect-tier 'product-layer
  :verbs-added  ((verb :name 'irrigate :domain 'baobab)
                 (verb :name 'sunrise   :domain 'baobab))
  :books-added  ((book :name 'baobab :chapters 12))
  :cards-shared 47
  :promotion-proposal
                (proposal :type 'promote-verb
                           :verb 'irrigate
                           :to 'core-tier
                           :rationale \"10k+ operators use it\")
  :signed-by    'baobab-team
  :signed-at    #inst \"2026-07-12T10:00:00Z\")
```

Head: `subscriber`. Each fork declares itself and what it adds.

## Dialect manifest

```motoi-scheme
(dialect-manifest
  :name         'baobab-scheme
  :parent       'motoi-scheme
  :parent-hash  \"sha256:...\"          ; anchors to a specific Motoi Scheme version
  :additions    ((verb 'irrigate) (verb 'sunrise) (book 'baobab))
  :removals     '()                    ; can only add
  :renames      '()                    ; renames on the boundary layer only
  :promotion-candidates '(irrigate))
```

A dialect can ADD but not REMOVE from its parent. This keeps
compatibility monotone.

## Promotion proposals

When a community verb has proven itself, it can be proposed for
promotion to the core.

```motoi-scheme
(promotion-proposal
  :verb           'irrigate
  :from-dialect   'baobab-scheme
  :to             'motoi-scheme-core
  :usage-count    10847
  :subscribers    47
  :incident-narrative
                  \"in-promotion-irrigate-2026-07-12\"
  :rationale      \"operator utility across 47 downstream projects\"
  :risks          '((namespace-conflict weight))
  :status         'review)
```

Core team reviews. If accepted, the verb migrates to core; if
rejected, it stays in the dialect.

## Card sharing

Cards ARE shareable. SLATs are local by default (per the two-tier
doctrine). Community carts get an explicit share manifest:

```motoi-scheme
(shared-cart
  :cart-hash    \"sha256:...\"
  :author       'jenn
  :dialect      'baobab-scheme
  :license      'lacuna-community-1.0
  :shared-at    #inst \"2026-07-12T09:00:00Z\"
  :description  \"irrigate the front garden every morning at 7am\"
  :tags         '(garden watering routine))
```

Shared cards are read-only. Downstream operators can copy + modify;
the original stays.

## Author identity

```motoi-scheme
(subscriber-author
  :handle       'jenn
  :ed25519-pub  \"pub-hex...\"
  :verified-at  #inst \"2026-07-12T08:00:00Z\"
  :verified-by  'lacuna-labs)
```

Ed25519-signed identity. Contributions carry the author's signature.

